# Making Decisions with `if`

Use `if` to execute code only when a condition is true.

```dart
if (condition) {
  // code when true
}
```

Optionally add `else if` and `else`.

```dart
if (score >= 90) {
  print('A');
} else if (score >= 80) {
  print('B');
} else {
  print('C');
}
```

Conditions must be boolean expressions.

quizData.question:
What will the following code print?
```dart
int x = 5;
if (x = 5) {
  print('equal');
}
```

